title.narrative: 70 business plans approved by the External Committee

comment.narrative: Higher than target reflects efforts to compensate RPOs with smaller size.

title.narrative: Quarterly reports completed and sent to Bank
Satisfcatory technical and financial audits of the Project
By EOP, at least a 25% increase in sales receipts of small-scale producers via PRORURAL-financed productive alliances

baseline.value: Pre-project sales receipts of Rural Producer Associations

target.value: 25% increase in pre-project sales receipts for rural producer associations.

comment.narrative: This amount indicates the increase in sales calculated as of this date.

title.narrative: 140 RPAs trained and capable of participating in productive alliances.
At least 100 productive alliances proposed with quality Business Plans according to criteria set forth in Project Operational Manual.
5,000 small-scale producers participating in PRORURAL-financed productive alliances.
85% satisfaction among RPAs regarding technical assistance from certified service providers.

baseline.value: Annual Operating Plan for 2008 totaling US$9.1 million received no objection from Bank.

title.narrative: The M&E system reports satisfactory results for the financed Business Plans.

comment.narrative: A web based monitoring system (PENTAGON) is operational.

title.narrative: By EOP, at least 30 technical service providers (TSPs) trained and certified to provide technical assistance to RPAs and productivealliances.
Productive alliances continue to operate one year after having received the support of the project and have a functioning revolvingfund

comment.narrative: This indicator will be measurable starting in June 2013.

title.narrative: By EOP, at least a 20% increase in membership in RPAs for the project area, relative to baseline.
Percentage of sub-project area that, as an effect of the project, was converted to tree plantation for multiple sustainable uses
